The course will combine lectures with seminars and  written homework (desk research, self-reflections, discussion papers). The course will end with a reflection paper: a student will demonstrate his or her understandings of family and childhood frameworks from the angles that had been discussed during the course.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course is aimed to develop awareness in the topics related to contemporary families and childhoods. A specific focus in this course will be put on children and their subjective well-being in local and international perspectives.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student passing the course: 
*	acknowledges differences between the notions of the family and childhood in research and policies;
*	understands children as a social group in a generational order and in their own right;
*	acknowledges the children's perspectives and its value in research and practice;
*       discusses ethical problems and dilemmas by studying families and childhoods
